text: Durango City (Tepehuan: Korian), officially Victoria de Durango and also known as Ciudad de Durango, is the capital and largest city of Durango, Mexico. It stands at an altitude of . In 2010, the city had a total population of 518,709, up from 463,830 in 2005. It serves as municipal seat of Durango Municipality which had a population of 582,267 in 2010. ==References== Category:Settlements in Durango Category:Capital cities in Mexico Category:1563 establishments Category:16th-century establishments in Mexico
